## Project Description
The huge solar farms being created in Nevada can provide opportunities to explain how solar works, why it helps Nevada's RPS (renewable portfolio standard), reduce our greenhouse gas emissions and reduce our air pollution.  These concepts can be communicated in an interesting, lively environment that will inspire the imagination for all citizens in Nevada and more.  

Nevada has progressively passed legislation to move our RPS from 25% to 50% by 2030.  We will see more and continued development of solar farms in our surrounding BLM (Bureau of Land Management) land.  

With partnerships with the energy investment companies we can arrange the layout and design of these solar arrays to create an inviting, interesting center for STEAM projects.

A couple of the specific items we would look to establish are:
-Create a multidimensional and cross-disciplinary STEAM concept into sustainability and community engagement
-Design of the solar array creating an accessible community and educational space.
-Establishing a pollinator-friendly solar scorecards for Southern Nevada.
-Setup the use of the modeling tool InVEST(Integrated Valuation of Ecosystem Services and Trade-offs) to augment natural resource management.
-Partnerships with local environmental organizations to incorporate Geographic Information Systems (GIS) to bring the generation of climate change into direct involvement.


