# Additional Information
InVEST (Integrated Valuation of Ecosystem Services and Trade-offs) is a suite of free, open-source software models used to map and value the goods and services from nature that sustain and fulfill human life.  Out of Stanford university this modeling tool uses data about the environment to explore how changes in ecosystems are likely to affect the flow of benefits to people. It is designed to inform decisions about natural resource management.

